<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 16 at 4:12AM CST  by NWS Brownsville</headline>
<description>Local Media is reporting light icing on some elevated bridges and
overpasses along Interstate Highway 2 between Mercedes and La
Feria. National Weather Service Doppler radar is indicating very
light rain or drizzle across portions of the Mid and Lower Rio
Grande. Observations across the region show temperatures ranging
from 27-32 degrees. Patchy light icing with trace accumulations
along elevated surfaces will persist through sunrise. Light
precipitation is expected to end by 6 AM.
Motorists are urged to drive with caution and slow down over
bridges or wet surfaces until temperatures rise above freezing
around 10 AM.</description>
